-- Wells Fargo names Stumpf CEO; Kovacevich stays chair
-- 
-- Wed Jun 27, 2007 7:14am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/27/us-wellsfargo-idUSWNAS476720070627

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Wells Fargo & Co. ( WFC.N ), the fifth-largest U.S. bank, on Wednesday named John Stumpf chief executive, effective immediately, replacing Richard Kovacevich, who will remain chairman. 

 Stumpf, 53, has been chief operating officer and was long considered a leading candidate to replace Kovacevich. Kovacevich has said he would remain with the company no later than the end of 2008, when he will be 65.